{"title_page": "Dipturus lamillai", "text_new": "{{short description|Species of skate}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| status = \n| status_system = \n| status_ref = \n| image = \n| taxon = Dipturus lamillai\n| display_parents = \n| authority = (Concha, Caira, Ebert & Pompert, 2019)\n| synonyms = \n}}\n\n'''''Dipturus lamillai''''' is a species of long-snout skate of the genus [[Dipturus]]. It was first described in 2019 after it was found in waters near the [[Falkland Islands]] in the southwest [[Atlantic Ocean]].<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Francisco Concha |author2=Janine Caira |author3=David Ebert |author4=Joost Pompert |title=Redescription and taxonomic status of Dipturus chilensis (Guichenot, 1848), and description of Dipturus lamillai sp. nov. (Rajiformes: Rajidae), a new species of long-snout skate from the Falkland Islands |journal=[[Zootaxa]] |date=1 May 2019 |volume=4590 |issue=5 |pages=501-524 |url=https://www.biotaxa.org/Zootaxa/article/view/zootaxa.4590.5.1 |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Dipturus lamillai CONCHA, CAIRA, EBERT & POMPERT, 2019 |url=https://shark-references.com/species/view/Dipturus-lamillai |website=Shark References |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref> The population had previously been recorded as ''[[Zearaja chilensis]]'', the Chilean yellow-nosed skate, but had been suspected to be a separate [[cryptic species]], one that looks identical to another species but has distinct genetic information. It was named in honour of [[Julio Lamilla]], a Chilean biologist.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dipturus lamillai: A new species of Long-snout Skate from the Falkland Islands |url=http://sciencythoughts.blogspot.com/2019/08/dipturus-lamillai-new-species-of-long.html |website=Sciency Thoughts |accessdate=19 March 2020 |date=8 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q78912864}}\n\n[[Category:Dipturus]]\n[[Category:Species described in 2019]]\n[[Category:Fish of the Atlantic Ocean]]\n\n{{rajiformes-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Species of amphipod}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| status = \n| status_system = \n| status_ref = \n| image = \n| taxon = Dipturus lamillai\n| display_parents = \n| authority = (Concha, Caira, Ebert & Pompert, 2019)\n| synonyms = \n}}\n\n'''''Dipturus lamillai''''' is a species of long-snout skate of the genus [[Dipturus]]. It was first described in 2019 after it was found in waters near the [[Falkland Islands]] in the southwest [[Atlantic Ocean]].<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Francisco Concha |author2=Janine Caira |author3=David Ebert |author4=Joost Pompert |title=Redescription and taxonomic status of Dipturus chilensis (Guichenot, 1848), and description of Dipturus lamillai sp. nov. (Rajiformes: Rajidae), a new species of long-snout skate from the Falkland Islands |journal=[[Zootaxa]] |date=1 May 2019 |volume=4590 |issue=5 |pages=501-524 |url=https://www.biotaxa.org/Zootaxa/article/view/zootaxa.4590.5.1 |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Dipturus lamillai CONCHA, CAIRA, EBERT & POMPERT, 2019 |url=https://shark-references.com/species/view/Dipturus-lamillai |website=Shark References |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref> The population had previously been recorded as ''[[Zearaja chilensis]]'', the Chilean yellow-nosed skate, but had been suspected to be a separate [[cryptic species]], one that looks identical to another species but has distinct genetic information. It was named in honour of [[Julio Lamilla]], a Chilean biologist.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dipturus lamillai: A new species of Long-snout Skate from the Falkland Islands |url=http://sciencythoughts.blogspot.com/2019/08/dipturus-lamillai-new-species-of-long.html |website=Sciency Thoughts |accessdate=19 March 2020 |date=8 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q78912864}}\n\n[[Category:Dipturus]]\n[[Category:Species described in 2019]]\n[[Category:Fish of the Atlantic Ocean]]\n\n{{rajiformes-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Gazamp", "label": "safe", "comment": "Cleanup", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dipturus_lamillai"}
